[2] South Carolina - raccoon, human exposure
Date: Tue 11 Oct 2016
Source: Aiken Standard [edited]
http://www.aikenstandard.com/20161011/161019926/baby-raccoon-in-beaufort-county-potentially-exposes-two-to-rabies


A baby raccoon in Beaufort County has exposed 2 people to rabies, according to the South Carolina [SC] Department of Health and Environmental Control [DHEC].

SC DHEC said in a news release 2 people have started post-exposure treatment after the baby raccoon tested positive for rabies.

DHEC said a victim picked up the juvenile raccoon on 29 Sep 2016 on the side of the road near the Beaufort Town Center. The victims were exposed while providing care for the animal, when the raccoon began acting abnormally, DHEC said.

The raccoon was submitted to DHEC's lab on 30 Sep 2016, and was confirmed to have rabies the following day.

There have been 11 animals in Beaufort County to test positive for rabies in 2016, with 79 confirmed cases of animal rabies statewide.

[Byline: Maayan Schechter]

