[4] Pennsylvania - bat, human exposure
Date: Fri 14 Oct 2016
Source: Philly.com [edited]
http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/real-time/Bethlehem-girl-bitten-by-rabid-bat.html


A Bethlehem [Pennsylvania] teen is undergoing treatment for rabies after she picked up a sick bat and was bitten.

The 14-year-old girl was in Monocacy Park on 10 Oct 2016 when she tried to assist what she believed to be an injured bird, according to a story on LehighValleyLive.

Family members placed the bat into a box and rushed the girl to an area hospital, where she was immediately given the 1st dose in a series of vaccines to prevent her from contracting the rabies virus. The bat later tested positive for rabies, according to the story.

[Byline: Mari A. Schaefer]

